    terms:description "The crude phosphine intermediate was dissolved in ethanol (150 mL), and cooled to 0 Â°C. Under vigorous stirring, a solution of hydrogen peroxide (3.95 g, 3.50 mL, 40.7 mmol, 35%, 4.48 equiv), and glacial acetic acid (1.91 g, 1.80 mL, 30.5 mmol, 3.36 equiv) in ethanol (15.0 mL) was added drop-wise over 15 min. The mixture was stirred for 2 h at 0 Â°C, and was then refluxed for 2 h." ;
